&quot;Is there not something rather bizarre about the government taxing the money it&#x27;s giving to you to support your studies?&quot;
Not at all. Its just like mp&#x27;s, staff and everyone else employed by the government.<p>&quot;I&#x27;m not sure how it works in the Netherlands, but in the UK you can claim unemployment benefits without having to have been paying taxes (so far as I&#x27;m aware).&quot;
No, in the UK and the Netherlands they won&#x27;t hand out money to unemployed foreigners who choose to come and live there.<p>&quot;That&#x27;s the only difference I can see between a grant system and a salaried one.&quot;
You can still get a grant. Lucky you!!
